<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/972> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #972" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Used fines from usurers to dedicate sacred equipment and pave a street (Liv. 10.23.11-12)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/949> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #949" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Carried the Ogulnian law which opened the pontificate and the augurate to the plebeians and added four and five plebeian places, respectively, to the existing colleges of four patricians each (Liv. 10.6-9.2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1139> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1139" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Appointed to celebrate the Latin Festival (Fast. Cap., Degrassi 42f., 116, 434f.)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1099> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1099" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. ([- - - -] Gallus; Fabius' name entire); Plin. NH 33.44; Eutrop. 2.16; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd. (Gallo Sabino et Pisone); Chr. Pasc.; Zon. 8.7; Degrassi, 40f., 114, 432f. Both Consuls campaigned in Bruttium against a Samnite brigand, Lollius (Zon. 8.7; cf. Dion. Hal. 20.17). Pliny places the beginning of the silver coinage in this consulship (33.44; cf. Jerome, Chr. ad ann. 271, p. 130 Helm). A revolt in Picenum remained for their successors to quell (Eutrop. 2.16)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1098> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1098" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "For the filiation of Ogulnius, see Fast. Cap. for 257." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1089> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1089" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent with Gurges as head to the court of Ptolemy Philadelphus (Dion. Hal. 20.14; Val. Max. 4.3.9; cf. Liv. Per. 14; Iustin. 18.2.9; Dio fr. 41; Zon. 8.6)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1009> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1009" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent as head of a commission of 10 Legates to bring the serpent of Asclepius from Epidaurus to Rome (Val. Max. 1.8.2; Auct. Vir. Ill. 22.1; cf. Liv. 10.47.6-7; Per. 11; Ovid Metam. 15.622ff.; Plut. RQ 94; Lact. Inst. Div. 2.8)." .
